law.text:
As used in KRS 156.551 to 156.555, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Center" means the Center for Middle School Academic Achievement;
"Fund" means the Teachers' Professional Growth Fund;
"Middle school" means grades five (5) through eight (8), regardless of school or district configuration; and
"Reliable, replicable research" means objective, valid, scientific studies that:
Include rigorously defined samples of subjects that are sufficiently large and representative to support the general conclusions drawn;
Rely on measurements that meet established standards of reliability and validity;
Test competing theories, where multiple theories exist; and
Are subjected to peer review before results are published.
